The paper discusses the use of neural networks for real-time applications and proposes a method for accelerating the training of small and fast student networks using knowledge distillation from a large and accurate teacher network. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Given the focus on machine learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI. The use of conditional adversarial networks may also suggest a potential connection to generative models (cs.GT) or computer graphics (cs.GR), but these are less likely given the emphasis on knowledge distillation and network acceleration.
